The variable n is initialized with 100 according to the input.
It checks if the value of variable n is equal to 1, if it is, it prints the character 'a' as output.
If the value of variable n is equal to 2, it prints the string "ab" as output.
If the value of variable n is equal to 3, it prints the string "abc" as output.
If the value of variable n is greater than 3, it enters a for loop and it iterates from 0 to n/4.
Inside the for loop, it prints the string "abcd" n/4 times.
After the loop finishes, it calculates the remainder of n divided by 4, which is stored in variable t.
It checks if the value of variable t is equal to 1, if it is, it prints the character 'a' as output.
If the value of variable t is equal to 2, it prints the string "ab" as output.
If the value of variable t is equal to 3, it prints the string "abc" as output.
